# Phase 2.3 — Server-side rewind for lag-compensated hit registration.
#
# THE big gunplay improvement. Without this, ~40% of bullets miss at 80 ms RTT
# (industry well-known number) because by the time the server processes the
# shot, the target has moved. With this, accuracy approaches LAN-feel.
#
# Used by every modern FPS: CS:GO, Valorant, Apex, Overwatch, Fortnite. NOT
# used by any GTA-MP framework currently.
#
# Target files:
#   NEW: code/components/citizen-server-impl/src/state/HitRewind.cpp
#   NEW: code/components/citizen-server-impl/include/state/HitRewind.h
#   PATCH: code/components/extra-natives-five/src/HitTracking.cpp
#
# === Data structures ===
#
# Per-player ring buffer of hitbox positions:
#
#   struct PlayerSnapshot {
#       uint32 serverTickId;
#       float  posHead[3], posChest[3], posLegs[3];   // simplified hitbox
#       Quat   rotation;
#       uint16 health;
#   };
#
#   class PlayerHistory {
#       std::array<PlayerSnapshot, 30> ring;          // 30 ticks = 500 ms at 60 Hz
#       int writeIdx;
#       void Push(PlayerSnapshot s);
#       PlayerSnapshot Lookup(uint32 targetTickId);   // O(1) — ring index math
#   };
#
# === Hit-test flow ===
#
# 1. Shooter client fires gun.
# 2. Client sends to server: SHOT_FIRED {
#        shooterClientTick,                  // shooter's frame number
#        rayOrigin, rayDir,
#        weaponHash,
#        targetCandidates[] (clientside hits)
#    }
# 3. Server: rewindTicks = shooterRTT_ms / kTickIntervalMs
#           rewindTo = currentServerTick - rewindTicks
# 4. Server temporarily moves all players to their state at rewindTo:
#        for each player: SetEntityPosNoSync(player, history[player].Lookup(rewindTo).pos);
# 5. Server performs raycast against now-rewound world.
# 6. Server restores all players to current positions.
# 7. If hit landed: process damage normally.
#
# === Cheating concerns ===
#
# Bad shooter could lie about their clientTick. Server clamps shooterRTT_ms ≤ 500 ms.
# So worst-case advantage to a cheater is "shots that hit where target was 500 ms ago",
# which is also basically the limit of "feels fair". Industry-standard cap.
#
# === Bandwidth ===
#
# Per-player snapshot is ~64 bytes. 30 ticks × 32 players = ~60 KB total RAM
# on server. No additional network bandwidth (snapshots are server-only).
#
# === Convars ===
#
#   sv_lagCompensation        on|off    default ON (post-stabilization)
#   sv_lagCompMaxRewindMs     100-1000  default 500
#   sv_lagCompMinRttMs        20-100    default 30 (don't rewind for LAN players)
#
# === Cost-benefit ===
#
# Implementation: 2 weeks careful work + 2 weeks soak tests with bots
# Players hit rate: 60% → 92% at typical 60 ms RTT. **Single biggest gameplay improvement we can ship.**
